DataElement.preferredName: Caries Occlusal Surface Dental Pulp Length Maximum Measurement
DataElement.preferredDefinition: the largest possible measurement related to length of the biting surfaces of the premolar and molar teeth to the pulp (a richly vascularized and innervated connective tissue of mesodermal origin contained in the central cavity of a tooth and delimited by the dentin) that has the decay of a tooth, in which it becomes softened, discolored, and/or porous.

Concepts.definition: The biting surfaces of the premolar and molar teeth.

A richly vascularized and innervated connective tissue of mesodermal origin contained in the central cavity of a tooth and delimited by the dentin. It has formative, nutritive, sensory, and protective functions.
The linear extent in space from one end of something to the other end, or the extent of something from beginning to end.
